"This was a massive potential banana skin. I said to the players 'don't get complacent, make sure that we make it difficult for them' but all that went out of the window in the first 15-20 minutes.
"The players showed great resolve in coming back and we scored at a good time.
"The sending off was completely the right decision.
"We really took advantage of them only having 10 players."
